  <discussion>Takakia ceratophylla appears to be somewhat tolerant of desiccation.  Frequently it grows with other drought-tolerant bryophytes such as Andreaea and Gymnomitrion.  The shoots are more rigid than those of T. lepidozioides, and leaf arrangement is more regular.  Rhizomatous shoots are predominantly subterranean.</discussion>
